                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has the announcement this morning in Case 13-1402, Kerry v. Din."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.087,
                        "stop": 297.12,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.087,
                                "stop": 15.848,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case is here on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.848,
                                "stop": 23.594,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Petitioner Fauzia Din is a naturalized citizen and resident of the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.594,
                                "stop": 30.812,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Her husband Kanishka Berashk is a citizen and resident of Afghanistan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.812,
                                "stop": 37.562,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "He was also a civil servant in that country\u0027s government while it was under the control of the Taliban."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.562,
                                "stop": 48.795,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "After Din was naturalized, she petitioned to have Berashk classified as an immediate relative entitled to priority immigration status."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.795,
                                "stop": 55.146,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The petition was granted, but Berashk\u0027s visa application was ultimately denied."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.146,
                                "stop": 70.944,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A consular officer informed him that he was deemed inadmissible under 8 U.S.C. \u00a71182(a)(3)(B), which excludes aliens who have engaged in terrorist activities."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.944,
                                "stop": 75.462,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But they declined to provide any further information."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.462,
                                "stop": 82.253,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Din sued in Federal District Court. The District Court dismissed her complaint, but the Ninth Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.253,
                                "stop": 105.901,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It held that Din had a protected liberty interest in her marriage that entitled her to review of the denial of Berashk\u0027s visa and that the government deprived her of that liberty interest without due process of law when it denied Berashk\u0027s visa application without a more detailed explanation of its reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.901,
                                "stop": 115.696,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Fifth Amendment provides that no person shall be \u201cdeprived of life, liberty or property without due process of law.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.696,
                                "stop": 131.969,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Thus, when one claims that his right to due process has been violated, a Court must first determine whether he has been deprived of life, liberty or property, and only then can it ask whether the process afforded was adequate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.969,
                                "stop": 140.775,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Din does not claim that the government\u0027s denial of her husband\u0027s visa application deprived her of life or property for obvious reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.775,
                                "stop": 160.457,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "At the time of the founding, however, liberty was understood to encompass only the power of, quoting from Blackstone, \u0022removing one\u0027s person to whatsoever place one\u0027s own inclination may direct, without imprisonment or restraint.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.457,
                                "stop": 168.527,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "So understood, Din has not been deprived of liberty either, and that is enough to resolve this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.527,
                                "stop": 176.808,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This Court has attempted to broaden the meaning of liberty in the Due Process Clause to include certain implied fundamental rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.808,
                                "stop": 183.128,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Even if one accepts this textually insupportable doctrine, Din\u0027s claim still fails."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.128,
                                "stop": 210.531,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Although some of our case law speaks of an implied fundamental right to marry, Din has not been forbidden to enter a marriage, and those right to marry cases cannot be expanded to include the right that Din argues for, namely the right to live in the United States with one\u0027s alien spouse, because we identify implied rights, not by looking to our case law, but by looking to this country\u0027s history and traditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.531,
                                "stop": 223.261,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Since Congress first began regulating immigration, it has placed serious constraints on the ability of immigrants to bring their relatives, including their spouses, into this country with them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 223.261,
                                "stop": 238.91,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Even when it showed preferences for immigrants with citizen relatives; for example, exempting them from immigration quotas or allocating quota spots in a manner that favored them, these were far from categorical rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 238.91,
                                "stop": 253.515,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This history belies any suggestion that Din has been deprived of an interest so fundamental that it is as our cases say it must be \u201cimplicit in the concept of ordered liberty.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.515,
                                "stop": 259.017,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Ninth Circuit is vacated, and the case remanded for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.017,
                                "stop": 264.372,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice and Justice Thomas join in this plurality opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.372,
                                "stop": 271.095,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment, which Justice Alito has joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 271.095,
                                "stop": 297.12,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has filed a dissenting opinion, which Justices Goldberg, Sotomayor, and Kagan have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
